# Project Conventions

## Architecture

Backend-only REST API: `Client → Express API → PostgreSQL`

## Layer Structure

```
src/
  routes/         # Route definitions and endpoint mapping
  controllers/    # Request handling, response formatting
  middleware/     # Auth (JWT), validation (Zod), error handling
  db/             # Connection pool, queries, migrations
  utils/          # Shared helpers, constants, type definitions
  types/          # Shared TypeScript interfaces and types
  app.ts          # Express app setup
  server.ts       # Entry point, starts listening
tests/              # All tests — mirrors src/ structure
  unit/             # Unit tests (mocked dependencies)
  integration/      # Integration tests (real test db)
  helpers/          # Test factories, utilities, mocks
  setup.ts          # Global test setup
```

## Conventions

- Each layer only imports from the layer below it (routes → controllers → db)
- Controllers never access `req`/`res` directly in business logic — delegate to service helpers or db layer
- All responses follow consistent JSON format: `{ data }` on success, `{ error, statusCode }` on failure
- Environment config via `dotenv` and `custom-env` — never hardcode secrets
- Use UUID for all primary keys
- Use snake_case for database columns, camelCase for TypeScript variables
